WEBVTT

00:00.450 --> 00:07.622
Today we continue our series, The Light is Coming, and nothing will be the same.

00:08.624 --> 00:15.335
And we continue the series with the theme when light moves into the neighborhood.

00:18.740 --> 00:24.530
Join me now in the reading of the Gospel lesson from Matthew, the first chapter

00:25.122 --> 00:27.425
8 verses 18 through 25.

00:28.527 --> 00:31.050
Please stand for the reading of the gospel.

00:31.130 --> 00:32.412
It will be on your screens.

00:32.452 --> 00:44.509
You are also invited to open your electronic devices and Bibles and join me in the gospel of Matthew verses 18 through 25.

00:45.330 --> 00:53.522
Now the birth of Jesus, the Messiah took place in this way.

00:54.498 --> 01:04.311
When his mother Mary had been engaged to Joseph, but before they lived together, she was found to be pregnant from the Holy Spirit.

01:05.893 --> 01:16.847
Her husband Joseph, being a righteous man and unwilling to expose her to public disgrace, planned to divorce her quietly.

01:19.050 --> 01:22.034
But just when he had resolved to do this,

01:22.882 --> 01:35.056
An angel of the Lord appeared to him in a dream and said, Joseph, son of David, do not be afraid to take Mary as your wife.

01:35.998 --> 01:40.142
For the child conceived in her is from the Holy Spirit.

01:41.184 --> 01:49.874
She will bear a son and you are to name him Jesus, for he will save his people from their sins.

01:51.010 --> 01:56.017
All this took place to fulfill what had been spoken by the Lord through the prophet.

01:57.699 --> 02:09.375
Look, the virgin shall become pregnant and give birth to a son, and they shall name him Immanuel, which means God is with us.

02:10.997 --> 02:16.825
When Joseph awoke from sleep, he did as the angel of the Lord commanded him.

02:17.847 --> 02:20.210
He took her as his wife.

02:21.186 --> 02:26.694
but had no marital relations with her until she had given birth to a son.

02:26.754 --> 02:32.141
And Joseph named him Jesus.

02:33.743 --> 02:36.527
This is the word of God for the people of God.

02:36.547 --> 02:38.550
Thanks be to God.

02:39.071 --> 02:39.812
Let us pray.

02:41.034 --> 02:42.636
Lord, here we are to worship.

02:42.736 --> 02:44.799
Here we are to bow down.

02:44.879 --> 02:50.066
Here we are to say that you are indeed our worthy and holy God.

02:50.882 --> 02:54.326
We have not gathered in this place to hear a word from Jasmine.

02:55.147 --> 03:02.376
We have gathered in this place expecting you to speak to our hearts and our minds and our souls.

03:02.476 --> 03:07.002
So speak, Lord, for your servants are listening.

03:08.584 --> 03:14.671
Hide this, your servant behind that old rugged cross so that everything that is said and everything that is done comes straight from you.

03:14.912 --> 03:20.178
Oh God, this is our servant's prayer in the name of Jesus, the Christ we pray.

03:21.058 --> 03:21.599
Amen.

03:23.002 --> 03:23.683
You may be seated.

03:29.675 --> 03:35.547
When I was a little kid, there was an epic snowstorm in Atlanta.

03:36.749 --> 03:43.122
We lived in one of those western neighborhoods where the

03:43.202 --> 03:47.886
the curb was about this thick and it was lined with granite.

03:47.947 --> 03:52.531
Anybody remember old Atlanta with those tall thick curves?

03:55.213 --> 04:01.039
So when it iced over, we had a literal ice rink on our street.

04:02.200 --> 04:12.690
The ice was thick, Mike, and all the kids came running out of their homes and using whatever they could to

04:12.770 --> 04:14.772
Ice skate, Lisa.

04:14.792 --> 04:22.241
We had roller blades and wagons and bicycles.

04:22.361 --> 04:39.602
I don't know why we thought we were going to ride bicycles on ice, but anything that had wheels or anything that we could turn into a sled became a tool for ice sledding and ice skating.

04:41.570 --> 04:46.816
It's amazing what a kid can come up with if you just let their imagination run wild.

04:48.839 --> 05:01.294
It's amazing what we could do if we threw away the rules that keep us bound and allow God to give us tools to do extraordinary things.

05:03.777 --> 05:04.238
You know what?

05:05.559 --> 05:07.662
That day I met people I'd never met.

05:09.644 --> 05:11.186
Everybody was outside.

05:11.650 --> 05:18.836
the people who drove into their garages and you never saw them, you finally got to meet them in the ice skating rink.

05:19.076 --> 05:22.279
The people who had opposite hours, maybe they worked at night.

05:22.319 --> 05:31.527
Well, you were gone during the day, they were home, but you never really got a chance to talk to them because they had opposite hours and you never saw them.

05:31.868 --> 05:39.434
And even the neighbors who were, you know, a little bit introverted and didn't really want to talk to other neighbors, bless God.

05:40.235 --> 05:41.636
They came out and

05:41.616 --> 05:55.677
And they for took and somebody brought out some coffee and then somebody brought out some hot chocolate and then somebody brought out some snacks and everybody began to join together.

05:55.697 --> 06:10.098
And instead of houses on a street, strangers that travel in the same way, it became a neighborhood.

06:12.770 --> 06:35.378
See, the difference between the place where you live in the neighborhood is that there are people there who you know and you are connected to and you are forming as a community, you are forming relationships, you are forming a way to be invited into a larger picture.

06:37.762 --> 06:43.133
If we say boarded up in our homes or in our safe places, we get what we call an echo chamber.

06:43.173 --> 06:45.598
We hear the same thing over and over again.

06:45.638 --> 06:47.723
We see the same thing over and over again.

06:48.063 --> 06:51.711
And we forget that there is life beyond us.

06:55.118 --> 06:58.866
Some of you know that I love national geographic.

07:00.322 --> 07:20.146
I always have, since we were little kids, some of you might remember, some of you are in my generation, some of you are parents of kids in the generation, that every month you could get a pack of cards with animals from National Geographic, and you had a big green case, we still have ours, and my mom's basement, yes, she wants me to get my stuff out of there.

07:22.569 --> 07:26.354
And he told you all about the animals each week.

07:29.762 --> 07:33.268
So now, I watch National Geographic on TV all the time.

07:34.390 --> 07:38.456
And there are a series of shows called Life Below Zero.

07:38.496 --> 07:46.009
And on Life Below Zero, we meet people who live all over Alaska.

07:47.371 --> 07:53.361
Did you know that Alaska just became a state in the United States in 1959?

07:55.064 --> 07:56.306
Recent history.

07:56.930 --> 08:09.338
And before that it was territory for indigenous people, people who were native to the land, people who had different tribes and different ways of being who lived off the land.

08:09.398 --> 08:16.274
Now they didn't necessarily have running water or lights to turn on, but they had light.

08:19.106 --> 08:30.999
They had light in relationships and how they gathered in their traditions and in the way that they lived, they could make fire out of nothing.

08:38.748 --> 08:42.052
But some of us believe that our ways are better than other people's ways.

08:44.575 --> 08:47.698
And we co-op and colonize.

08:48.642 --> 08:53.849
And we make people meld into our sense of what the neighborhood might be.

08:59.397 --> 09:03.903
One of the participants on Life Below Zero is Ask a Baskin.

09:03.963 --> 09:14.117
It's a type of indigenous Native American who lives in Alaska in the Tundra right below the tree line.

09:14.157 --> 09:17.682
Here in Georgia, we don't know what that is.

09:17.890 --> 09:25.540
because there are trees everywhere, but there is a line at the Arctic Circle where it is too cold for trees to grow.

09:25.580 --> 09:34.773
He said, in one of his interviews, he said, we used to fight over the land.

09:37.437 --> 09:41.763
All the different tribes, that was how we interacted with each other.

09:41.823 --> 09:44.306
We used to fight over the land.

09:45.474 --> 09:52.722
But in 1959, they came in Stoltlerland, and we don't have anything to fight about anymore.

09:55.005 --> 09:58.589
So we decided not to find a new thing to fight about.

10:00.551 --> 10:07.279
We decided that we would find a way to take care of each other.

10:11.844 --> 10:13.586
In the Gospel of Matthew,

10:14.722 --> 10:21.510
We find that Matthew chapter one starts with a long list of people.

10:22.911 --> 10:25.334
It's what we call a genealogy.

10:25.354 --> 10:39.570
It is a list that tells us how we get from David, how we get from Abraham to Jacob to Joseph to Ruth to David.

10:40.514 --> 10:45.722
To Uzziah, you remember in the year that King Uzziah died, I saw the Lord.

10:47.725 --> 11:06.354
To Solomon, to Jehoshaphat, to Hezekiah, to Amos, all the way to Joseph and Jesus.

11:09.314 --> 11:24.178
This neighborhood is made up of ordinary people who have done extraordinary things to allow us to see God keeps God's promise to us.

11:25.506 --> 11:30.411
Abraham is the answer to a promise and the receiver of a promise.

11:30.992 --> 11:36.398
His Jacob is the receiver of a promise that continues through Abraham.

11:36.858 --> 11:55.058
David is the receiver in the fruit of a promise that was first given to Abraham and on and on and on and Jesus becomes the ultimate answer to the promises of God from the prophet Isaiah that said, and there shall be a child.

11:56.674 --> 11:58.357
There shall be light.

11:59.779 --> 12:04.306
We shall call him wonderful counselor, Prince of Peace, mighty God.

12:04.366 --> 12:15.404
There shall be a little girl who is fresh with child.

12:18.029 --> 12:19.751
And she would not have done anything wrong.

12:22.275 --> 12:23.858
But people assume things.

12:24.642 --> 12:35.219
And they will assume that she has broken the rules that she has hung out with her dude Joseph way before she was supposed to.

12:40.107 --> 12:41.349
And they will want to punish her.

12:43.452 --> 12:47.058
Because those are the rules.

12:52.898 --> 12:54.609
And instead angels showed up.

12:57.064 --> 12:59.922
And they said two things that we ought not forget.

13:00.354 --> 13:22.724
They said, when God is with us, Emmanuel, I, Angel Gabriel, and all the other angels who have shown up and here to tell you that God is Emmanuel, that God is with us, that God never leaves us nor forsakes us, that when it is dark outside, God is at God's best to bring the light into the world.

13:27.710 --> 13:30.354
And the second thing they say is do not be afraid.

13:31.938 --> 13:33.681
I know what it looks like.

13:33.801 --> 13:35.483
I know what it feels like.

13:35.824 --> 13:39.550
I've seen the people counting their dollars in the grocery store line.

13:39.950 --> 13:43.456
I've seen the people sleeping outside on the church property.

13:43.956 --> 13:45.599
I know that times are hard.

13:45.919 --> 13:55.634
I've seen the layoff slips and all of the things that are going on, the gas prices, the grocery prices, I have seen the darkness.

14:02.850 --> 14:04.593
And God says, I am sending you light.

14:08.139 --> 14:15.110
Not just sending light, but I am sending you light.

14:16.773 --> 14:18.336
It has your name on it.

14:18.897 --> 14:22.002
It's coming to your neighborhood.

14:27.932 --> 14:29.234
And it's so personal.

14:31.554 --> 14:35.203
that I planned for it before you were even knit together in your mother's womb.

14:39.453 --> 14:46.770
I planned for this light even before you were aware that there was a difference between darkness and light.

14:47.138 --> 14:51.463
I planned for this even before you had bad days and good days.

14:51.823 --> 14:58.351
I planned for it even when people started shooting and when they started starving each other.

14:58.772 --> 15:02.976
I planned for it before any of this has happened.

15:13.709 --> 15:14.610
And Joseph.

15:17.058 --> 15:18.860
Don't worry about your plans.

15:23.104 --> 15:24.165
I've got plans.

15:29.550 --> 15:32.133
I want you to dig into for just a minute with me here.

15:32.433 --> 15:45.906
It says, in verse 19, her husband Joseph, being a righteous man and unwilling to expose her to public disgrace, plan to divorce her quietly.

15:47.106 --> 15:49.208
Wait a minute, I thought you said they were engaged.

15:51.771 --> 15:54.254
What does righteous mean?

15:55.395 --> 16:01.122
Well, back in that day, if you were engaged, you might as well have been married because the only way to get out of it was a divorce.

16:04.545 --> 16:12.434
And back in those days, if you were pregnant before you were married, even if you were engaged, you were to be stoned to death.

16:17.570 --> 16:20.519
But the text says that Joseph was a righteous man.

16:20.559 --> 16:30.610
That meant that Joseph thought that grace and mercy was more important than the rules.

16:33.634 --> 16:47.673
that Joseph understood that Jesus has come to fulfill the law, not to throw it over, but he comes in a different way than the Old Testament rules.

16:48.995 --> 16:53.942
The Old Testament rules say if she's pregnant and not married, stone her.

16:54.242 --> 16:57.466
The New Testament rules say, how do we love her?

17:00.871 --> 17:02.994
You feel the shift?

17:04.546 --> 17:06.775
Stone her, love her.

17:08.201 --> 17:12.338
Pre-Jesus, stone her, post-Jesus, love her.

17:19.170 --> 17:22.934
Joseph was a righteous man, and he was looking for a more excellent way.

17:22.994 --> 17:27.038
So he was just going to quietly divorce her so they didn't stone her, which was the law.

17:27.078 --> 17:30.742
And he could have taken the opportunity to bring up her on charges.

17:30.782 --> 17:33.025
And she would have been stoned to death.

17:33.245 --> 17:39.992
But even before the angel got ahold of him, he said, I'm just going to take care of you in this way, Mary.

17:40.052 --> 17:45.618
I'm going to quietly divorce you so that I can keep my world intact.

17:46.978 --> 17:50.287
But I also don't have to deal with your transgressions my whole life.

17:55.362 --> 17:56.646
But then the angels showed up.

17:57.468 --> 17:59.634
I told the kids the angels are my favorites.

18:00.642 --> 18:03.126
The angels showed up and it changed everything.

18:03.186 --> 18:05.209
Angels are messengers from God.

18:05.510 --> 18:09.516
We entertain angels all the time, unaware to us.

18:10.057 --> 18:11.479
Angels bring good news.

18:11.980 --> 18:14.584
Angels bring to us the rest of the story.

18:15.125 --> 18:19.632
Angels bring to us the solution before we even know what the problem is.

18:20.353 --> 18:20.894
Angels.

18:21.716 --> 18:23.218
You don't hear me this morning.

18:30.178 --> 18:42.854
The angel of the Lord appeared to him in a dream and said, Joseph's son of David, do not be afraid to take Mary as your wife or the child conceived in her is from the Holy Spirit.

18:44.035 --> 18:44.997
I'm sorry, what?

18:51.685 --> 18:52.366
The what?

18:55.470 --> 18:58.994
Because remember the Holy Spirit hasn't come yet in the New Testament.

19:02.786 --> 19:09.278
We know that the Holy Spirit was present at the beginning of time, but we don't have an awareness and a name for the Holy Spirit yet.

19:10.540 --> 19:15.149
And yet the angel says, Joseph, that child is from the Holy Spirit.

19:17.854 --> 19:26.770
And then the angel goes on to say, she will bear a son and you ought to name him Jesus, for he will save his people.

19:31.970 --> 19:45.770
And then Joseph being a good Jew, he can go through his Torah, Rolodex, and he can remember that in Isaiah it says, look, the virgin shall become pregnant and give birth to a son, and they shall call him Emmanuel, which means God with us.

19:49.675 --> 19:53.641
But just like the disciples later on, he knows it, but he doesn't know it.

19:56.986 --> 20:00.050
He's heard it, but it's not real.

20:05.186 --> 20:08.510
But when he woke up, he, something had changed.

20:10.512 --> 20:12.274
Light had moved into the neighborhood.

20:14.116 --> 20:18.921
There was a flashlight in the dark places, and it changed everything.

20:20.223 --> 20:25.148
And he did what the Lord commended him, and he took her as his wife, and they named him Jesus.

20:25.409 --> 20:26.971
Do you know what Jesus means?

20:29.193 --> 20:33.618
Jesus is actually Matthew's Greek version of Yeshua.

20:35.138 --> 20:35.899
What's Yeshua?

20:36.620 --> 20:37.381
Joshua.

20:39.183 --> 20:49.375
Do you remember that after Moses, there were two men who went into the promised land and they checked things out and they gave a minority report.

20:49.696 --> 20:53.300
All the other elders said, we can't go into the promised land, Mary.

20:53.600 --> 20:58.486
We can't go into the land that God has promised us where there will be milk and honey and all things will be well.

20:58.767 --> 21:01.490
We can't go there because there are scary people there.

21:04.482 --> 21:06.447
Joshua and Caleb.

21:06.467 --> 21:09.035
They said, no.

21:09.095 --> 21:11.221
It's good.

21:11.261 --> 21:13.748
It's good and we should go.

21:13.768 --> 21:15.773
It's good.

21:15.793 --> 21:16.957
We should go.

21:16.977 --> 21:18.962
Don't listen to them.

21:19.362 --> 21:21.865
The safe people want to stay safe.

21:22.526 --> 21:24.708
The sick people want to stay stuck.

21:24.729 --> 21:30.516
The people who don't like taking leaps and need a real firm sure thing.

21:30.876 --> 21:33.039
They want to stay in the wilderness.

21:33.379 --> 21:37.464
But we have seen the gift of the Lord ahead of us.

21:38.085 --> 21:40.708
We have seen the light in the neighborhood.

21:41.229 --> 21:45.714
We have seen the promises of God coming to fruition.

21:49.794 --> 21:54.319
Moses died before they went into the promised land.

21:55.640 --> 22:00.525
And Joshua took the people the rest of the way into the promised land.

22:05.550 --> 22:17.202
Jesus, Yeshua, Joshua, takes the people from darkness into light, takes the people from disaster to hope,

22:17.506 --> 22:40.018
takes the people from chaos to peace, takes the people from depression to joy, and takes the people from darkness to love.

22:44.930 --> 23:00.272
The old song said I moved from my old house and I moved from my old friends and I moved from my old way of life.

23:01.013 --> 23:10.226
They got I've moved out to a brand new life.

23:15.554 --> 23:20.081
When Joseph woke up, he did as the angel of the Lord commanded him.

23:22.364 --> 23:27.812
He took her as his wife, but had no marital relations with her until she had given birth to a son.

23:30.857 --> 23:42.514
And he named him Jesus, which means the Lord saves.

23:45.186 --> 23:54.226
to be continued this Wednesday at 6.30 PM as we celebrate Christmas Eve together.

